The paper focuses on autonomous navigation for mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses deep reinforcement learning (DRL) to learn the mapping from observation to action, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The input to the model is RGB images, which suggests the use of computer vision (cs.CV). The model is based on LSTM, which is a type of recurrent neural network, indicating the relevance to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments in both simulated and real environments, which implies the potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
